# security

- Store secrets (API tokens, passwords) in environment variables only; never commit them or echo them in logs/UI.
- Do not expose sensitive values in error messages, prompts, or client-side code.
- Validate and sanitize external input (HTTP params, JQL fragments if user-supplied, file paths). Prefer parameterized APIs over string concatenation for queries where applicable.

- Use `os.environ["VAR"]` or a `.env` file loaded via `python-dotenv`.
- Before adding a Python dependency, verify it has a release within the last 90 days
  and no unpatched CVEs on https://pypi.org or Snyk.
- Sanitize all user-supplied input before embedding it in JQL, SQL, or shell commands.
  Use parameterized queries or allowlist validation — never string concatenation.
  ```python
  # BAD
  jql = f"project = {user_input}"
  # GOOD
  jql = f"project = {sanitize_jql_value(user_input)}"
- Never log, return in HTTP responses, or display in UI: passwords, API tokens,
  connection strings, or secret keys. Mask or omit them entirely.
- Never log, any data which subjects KVKK, GDPR and GDPR UK
